adline.com/2017/02/carpool-karaoke-the-series-james-corden-will-smith-apple-music-seth-macfarlane-chelsea-handler-video-teaser-1201910376/|archive-date=December 1, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2017, Apple appointed Jamie Erlicht and Zack Van Amburg to head their newly formed worldwide video unit. By November, Apple confirmed that it was branching out into original scripted programming when announcing straight-to-series orders for two television programs: a drama series starring [[Jennifer Aniston]] and [[Reese Witherspoon]], and a reboot of the anthology series ''[[Amazing Stories (1985 TV series)#Reboot|Amazing Stories]]'' by [[Steven Spielberg]].<ref name=\"ScriptedSeries\">{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|title=Apple Gives Reese Witherspoon-Jennifer Aniston Morning Show Series 2-Season Order, Confirms 'Amazing Stories' Reboot|url=https://deadline.com/2017/11/apple-reese-witherspoon-jennifer-aniston-morning-show-series-2-season-order-amazing-stories-reboot-1202204293/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=November 30, 2017|date=November 8, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201034725/http://deadline.com/2017/11/apple-reese-witherspoon-jennifer-aniston-morning-show-series-2-season-order-amazing-stories-reboot-1202204293/|archive-date=December 1, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nApple is reportedly planning on spending around $1&nbsp;billion on original programming in the following years.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lieberman|first=David|title=Apple Plans To Spend $1B For Video Content Over The Next Year: Report|url=https://deadline.com/2017/08/apple-plans-spend-1b-video-content-1202149989/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]|accessdate=November 30, 2017|date=August 16, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171201033432/http://deadline.com/2017/08/apple-plans-spend-1b-video-content-1202149989/|archive-date=December 1, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> More recently, it has been projected that they will spend about $4.2&nbsp;billion on original programming by 2022.<ref>{{cite web|last=Wallenstein|first=Andrew|title=Apple Projected to Spend $4.2 Billion on Original Content by 2022|url=https://variety.com/2017/digital/news/apple-projected-to-spend-4-2-billion-on-original-content-by-2022-1202622459/|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|accessdate=December 3, 2017|date=November 24, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171128234842/http://variety.com/2017/digital/news/apple-projected-to-spend-4-2-billion-on-original-content-by-2022-1202622459/|archive-date=November 28, 2017|url-status=live}}</ref> In August 2019, it was reported that Apple had already spent over $6 billion on original programming.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cnbc.com/2019/08/19/apple-spending-6-billion-on-shows-trying-to-beat-disney-ft.html|title=Apple is spending $6 billion on original shows and trying to beat Disney+ to market, reports FT|last=Leswing|first=Kif|date=2019-08-19|website=CNBC|language=en|access-date=2020-02-21}}</ref>\n\nOn March 25, 2019, Apple announced their streaming service as [[Apple TV+]], along with the announcement of Apple's slate of original programming.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theverge.com/2019/3/25/18280920/apple-tv-streaming-service-announcement-price-date-launch-event-2019|title=Apple announces Apple TV Plus video subscription service|last=Welch|first=Chris|date=25 March 2019|work=[[The Verge]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190326150154/https://www.theverge.com/2019/3/25/18280920/apple-tv-streaming-service-announcement-price-date-launch-event-2019|archive-date=March 26, 2019|access-date=26 March 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> The service launched on November 1, 2019, in over 100 countries through the [[Apple TV (software)|Apple TV app]].\n\nOn 13 March 2020, Apple suspended all active filming on Apple TV+ shows due to the COVID-19 outbreak, and all production on series have been postponed indefinitely.<ref>https://www.macrumors.com/2020/03/13/apple-tv-plus-filming-suspended/</ref>\n\n==Original programming==\n\n===Original series===\n\n====Drama====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"width:100%;\"\n|-\n! Title\n! Genre\n! Premiere\n! Seasons\n! Length\n! Status\n|-\n| ''[[For All Mankind (TV series)|For All Mankind]]''\n| [[Alternate history]]\n| {{dts|November 1, 2019}}\n| {{sort|110|1 season, 10 episodes}}\n| {{sort|060|60 min.}}\n| Renewed<ref name=\"Renewed\"/>\n|-\n| ''[[The Morning Show (American TV series)|The Morning Show]]''\n| [[Drama (film and television)|Drama]]\n| {{dts|November 1, 2019}}\n| {{sort|110|1 season, 10 episodes}}\n| {{sort|060|60 min.}}\n| Renewed<ref name=\"Renewed\"/>\n|-\n| ''[[See (TV series)|See]]''\n| [[Science fiction]]\n| {{dts|November 1, 2019}}\n| {{sort|108|1 season, 8 episodes}}\n| {{sort|060|60 min.}}\n| Renewed<ref name=\"Renewed\"/>\n|-\n| ''[[Servant (TV series)|Servant]]''\n| [[Psychological thriller]]\n| {{dts|November 28, 2019}}\n| {{sort|110|1 season, 10 episodes}}\n| {{sort|030|30 min.}}\n| Renewed<ref>{{cite web|last=Andreeva|first=Nellie|title=M. Night Shyamala's 'Servant' Renewed For Season 2 By Apple Ahead Of Premiere|url=https://deadline.com/2019/11/m-night-shyamalan-servant-renewed-season-2-apple-ahead-of-premiere-1202793633/|work=[[Deadline Hollywood]]date=November 22, 2019||accessdate=November 23, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Truth Be Told (2019 TV series)|Truth Be Told]]''\n| [[Legal drama]]\n| {{dts|December 6, 2019}}\n| {{sort|108|1 season, 8 episodes}}\n| {{sort|045|45 min.}}\n| Renewed<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://apple-tv-plus-press.apple.com/en-US/news/2020/03/apple-renews-naacp-image-award-winning-series-truth-be-told/|title=Apple renews NAACP Image Award-winning series \u201cTruth Be Told\u201d - Apple|website=apple-tv-plus-press.apple.com|access-date=2020-03-05}}</ref>\n|-\n| ''[[Amazing Stories (2020 TV series)|Amazing Stories]]''\n| [[Science fiction]] [[Anthology series|anthology]]\n| {{dts|March 6, 2020}}\n| {{sort|110|1 season, 5 episodes}}\n| {{sort|050|50 min.}}\n| \n|-\n! colspa